{
  "texts": [
    "We notice that this data is also the data defining the associated bundle to the principal π 1 (B)-bundle B → B with respect to ρ.",
    "Hence, M ≃ B × ρ N. □ Remark 2.10.",
    "Comparing Example 2.8 and Proposition 2.9, we see that B × ρ H N and B × ρ N are isomorphic as twisted principal bundles; however, this isomorphism need not preserve the flat connections (the monodromy ρ H may have a non-trivial translational part).If M ≃ B × ρ N is as in Proposition 2.9, the adjoint bundle satisfies adM ≃ B × ρ 𝔫.",
    "It inherits a flat connection whose monodromy is still ρ (under the identification Aut(N) ≃ Aut(𝔫), assuming that N is simplyconnected).",
    "From the principal bundle situation one can deduce the following important correspondence: Proposition 2.11."
  ]
}